  "title": "Sonographer / Radiographer (Mammogram)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Perform all diagnostic imaging services according to standards described in SOP.</li>\n  <li>Ensure examination is performed to the correct patient and observes radiation safety rule and respective procedural consents described in SOP.</li>\n  <li>Ensure the quality of the film is optimal, it is correctly labeled and the examination requested has been completed before sending for reporting or providing as wet-film to patient.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that the examination code entered into the system corresponds to the examination requested.</li>\n  <li>Explain the examination to the patient, what he/she will be undergoing and the estimated duration of it.</li>\n  <li>Ensure patients’ safety, physical and emotional well-being is taken care of during and after the examination.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that precautions have been taken to protect patients, staff and public from unnecessary exposure to ionizing radiation.</li>\n  <li>Perform on-call and after hours duties when necessary, ensure prompt response which is in line with the prescribed standard of the Hospital.</li>\n  <li>Perform daily QA procedures on equipment according to manufacturers’ recommendations to ensure optimal performance of these equipment.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other duties as instructed by the Manager.</li>\n</ul>",
